          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The chemical composition of the glass fibres used in the rock wool production is similar to the composition of naturally cooled volcano basalt and has a composition listed in Tab.
3.1 and 3.2 in ecoinvent v2.2 report 16, part XIV. Rock wool contains: a minimum of 96% mineral fibres,between 0.5 and 3.0 weight percent of phenolic resin depending on the specific product characteristics, and about 0.2 percent mineral oil (ecoinvent v2.2 report 16, part XIV). An average composition of 1.8% phenolic resin, 0.2% mineral oil, and 98% mineral fibres has been assumed and used to calculate C content of the rock wool</comment>
